  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime. While embezzling $25,000 is a serious breach of trust by a professional accountant, mitigating factors include the lack of a prior criminal record and the partial restitution already made to the employer. A brief period of incarceration is warranted to serve as a deterrent and acknowledge the severity of the fiduciary breach, followed by a period of probation and a mandatory order to complete the remaining restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
}
